I looked into [this|https://www.mongodb.com/community/forums/t/golang-changestream-server-selector/119480] community forum post and I think it describes a real bug.

h2. Summary
Almost all operations use a composite server selector that includes a {{LatencySelector}} to filter out high-latency servers.

See [default {{Collection}} read selector|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-go-driver/blob/63855571587c4e7c7ba556410df182b3019208d6/mongo/collection.go#L89-L92]:
{code:go}
description.CompositeSelector([]description.ServerSelector{
	description.ReadPrefSelector(rp),
	description.LatencySelector(db.client.localThreshold),
})
{code}

However, the {{ChangeStream}} server selector seems to not use a {{LatencySelector}}, only a {{ReadPrefSelector}}.

See [{{ChangeStream}} selector|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-go-driver/blob/63855571587c4e7c7ba556410df182b3019208d6/mongo/change_stream.go#L111]:
{code:go}
cs := &ChangeStream{
	client:        config.client,
	registry:      config.registry,
	streamType:    config.streamType,
	options:       options.MergeChangeStreamOptions(opts...),
	selector:      description.ReadPrefSelector(config.readPreference),
	cursorOptions: config.client.createBaseCursorOptions(),
}
{code}

Is that intentional or a bug?

